g.title: noteD19670601
g.text: Early AGC programs had names that were
typically related to the sun, and
in the name, as in SUNSPOT, SUNDIAL,
why name them after the sun rather than
the moon? NASA had a different concern,
which was that nobody could remember
which of these programs went in the CM
and which in the LM. So NASA requested
that the CM program's name begin with
LUMINARY). After a few years, though,
MIT/IL apparently forgot the rule and
named the final CM program ARTEMIS.
